I needed GCC 13.3.0 to build linux kernel 6.10.5 as GCC15 was causing so many
build failures.

Below are the steps I followed to build GCC13.3.0,

Note : I am using arch linux.

1. [ ] mkdir compiler_build
2. [ ] cd compiler_build
3. [ ] wget https://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/gcc/gcc-13.3.0/gcc-13.3.0.tar.xz
4. [ ] sudo pacman -S --needed gmp mpfr libmpc isl
5. [ ] tar -xf gcc-13.3.0.tar.xz
6. [ ] cd gcc-13.3.0
7. [ ] mkdir build && cd build
8. Build only c and c++ compilers.

   [ ] ../configure --prefix=/opt/gcc13 \
       --enable-languages=c,c++ \
       --disable-multilib

9.  [ ] make -j$(nproc)
10. [ ] sudo make install
11. [ ] export PATH=/opt/gcc13/bin:$PATH  #My default shell is BASH
12. [ ] gcc --version
13. [ ] echo 'export PATH=/opt/gcc13/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
14. [ ] reboot now
15. [ ] gcc --version #Should be by default set to gcc13
16. [ ] rm -rf compiler_build #Delete the directory where we built compiler
